<subSubSection id="C3599AB95F50FFC3BBA35877BA82200F" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F50FFC3BBA35877BD082732" blockId="3.[151,1073,772,796]" box="[151,1073,772,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<heading id="D0B47E5E5F50FFC3BBA35877BD082732" box="[151,1073,772,796]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBA35877BB522732" bold="true" box="[151,619,772,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="4C43B2B15F50FFC3BBA35877B8742732" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[151,333,772,796]" class="Aves" family="Trochilidae" genus="Glaucis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBA35877B8742732" bold="true" box="[151,333,772,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Glaucis hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rufous-breasted Hermit
</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="1378D5B75F50FFC3B8C75877BD082732" box="[1011,1073,772,796]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[572,585,876,897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1058,246,855]" captionTargetId="figure-1545@4.[136,1059,226,856]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG 3 Glaucis hirsutus female, MHNG 1723.041." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5822974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5822974/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F50FFC3BBD7585ABA82200F" blockId="3.[151,1074,809,1281]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
Specimen MHNG 1723.041 is a female 
<taxonomicName id="4C43B2B15F50FFC3B9A6585ABA7A276F" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[658,835,809,833]" class="Aves" family="Trochilidae" genus="Glaucis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3B9A6585ABA7A276F" box="[658,835,809,833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Glaucis hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which exhibits an unusually strong coppery colouration dorsally (
<figureCitation id="1378D5B75F50FFC3B949583ABB85274F" box="[637,700,841,865]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[572,585,876,897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1058,246,855]" captionTargetId="figure-1545@4.[136,1059,226,856]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG 3 Glaucis hirsutus female, MHNG 1723.041." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5822974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5822974/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). According to the specimen label it was “collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F35489A25F50FFC3BA5B5819B8EB27AC" box="[367,466,874,898]" name="Paraguay" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
some time between 1983 and 1989” [with no indication of collector]. It does not have a field number and it was not included in the field reports available in the archives of the Museum. Unable to trace the specimen, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3B88258DAB80327CF" author="CLAY, R. P. &amp; DEL CASTILLO, H." pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2292" refString="CLAY, R. P. &amp; DEL CASTILLO, H. 2004. Annotated Checklist of the Birds of Paraguay. Guyra Paraguay, Asuncion. 200 pp." type="book" year="2004">Clay &amp; del Castillo (2004)</bibRefCitation>
list the species without comment in a list of “Possible Hypothetical” species. There are no other records for 
<collectingCountry id="F35489A25F50FFC3B96B5899BBFB202C" box="[607,706,1002,1026]" name="Paraguay" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and the species has never been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F35489A25F50FFC3BA055F7AB8A2200F" box="[305,411,1033,1057]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3BA9F5F7ABB07200F" author="CHEBEZ, J. C." box="[427,574,1033,1057]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" pagination="108 - 179" refId="ref2247" refString="CHEBEZ, J. C. 1996. Aves de la Provincia de Misiones (pp. 108 - 179). In: CHEBEZ J. C. (ed.). Fauna Misionera. LOLA, Buenos Aires, 318 pp." type="book chapter" year="1996">Chebez, 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3B9795F79BA92200F" author="MAZAR BARNETT, J. M. &amp; PEARMAN, M." box="[589,939,1033,1057]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2603" refString="MAZAR BARNETT, J. M. &amp; PEARMAN, M. 2001. Lista comentada de las aves Argentinas / Annotated checklist of the birds of Argentina. Lynx Ediciones, Barcelona, 164 pp." type="book" year="2001">Mazar Barnett &amp; Pearman, 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3599AB95F50FFC3BBD75F5ABA6A2187" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F50FFC3BBD75F5ABB86212F" blockId="3.[151,1074,809,1281]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="4C43B2B15F50FFC3BBD75F5AB8AE206F" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[227,407,1065,1089]" class="Aves" family="Trochilidae" genus="Glaucis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBD75F5AB8AE206F" box="[227,407,1065,1089]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Glaucis hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in tropical cis-Andean regions of the Neotropics from Panama to west-central (
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3B95D5F39BBCE204F" box="[617,759,1097,1121]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
) and south-east (
<taxonomicName id="4C43B2B15F50FFC3B88F5F3ABD10204F" authority="Paulo" authorityName="Paulo" box="[955,1065,1097,1121]" class="Gastropoda" family="Retusidae" genus="Sao" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">São Paulo</taxonomicName>
) Brazil (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3BBDD5F1AB8B520AF" author="GRANTSAU, R." box="[233,396,1129,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2458" refString="GRANTSAU, R. 1988. Os beija-flores do Brasil. Expressao e Cultura, Rio de Janeiro, 233 pp." type="book" year="1988">Grantsau, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3B93A5F19BA7F20AF" author="MEYER DE SCHAUENSEE, R." box="[526,838,1129,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2672" refString="MEYER DE SCHAUENSEE, R. 1982. A guide to the birds of South America. Intercollegiate Press, USA, 498 pp." type="book" year="1982">Meyer de Schauensee (1982)</bibRefCitation>
listed the distribution as “ 
<collectingCountry id="F35489A25F50FFC3BB8B5FFAB826208F" box="[191,287,1161,1185]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
south to 
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3BA4A5FFABB7A208F" box="[382,579,1161,1185]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
” [perhaps on the basis of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3B8605FFABAD2208F" author="RUSCHI, A." box="[852,1003,1161,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2904" refString="RUSCHI, A. 1979. Aves do Brasil. Editora Rios, Sao Paulo, 335 pp." type="book" year="1979">Ruschi (1979)</bibRefCitation>
which is cited in the bibliography] there are apparently no unambiguously documented records of the species anywhere in southern Brazil. The following summarises what has been published about the species in this region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F50FFC3BBD75E61BA6A2187" blockId="3.[151,1074,1297,1449]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBD75E61B8812107" box="[227,440,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3BBD75E61B8812107" box="[227,440,1297,1321]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
: It was not reported during a series of inventories in southwestern 
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3BBC65E41B8F52167" box="[242,460,1329,1353]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
immediately adjacent to the Paraguayan border (Straube 
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBA35E21B9F12147" box="[151,200,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
., 2006a, b; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3BA7E5E22BB212147" author="PIVATTO, M. A. C. &amp; MANCO, D. D. G. &amp; STRAUBE, F. C. &amp; FILHO, A. &amp; MILANO, M." box="[330,536,1361,1385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref2743" refString="PIVATTO, M. A. C., MANCO, D. D. G., STRAUBE, F. C., URBEN- FILHO, A. &amp; MILANO, M. 2006. Aves do Planalto da Bodoquena, estado do Mato Grosso do Sul (Brasil). Atualidades Ornitologicas 129: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pivatto 
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BAA95E21B8F72147" box="[413,462,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
) and although it is mapped for the extreme north of the state in the major field guide to the region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3B98F5E02BAA121A7" author="GWYNNE, J. A. &amp; RIDGELY, R. S. &amp; TUDOR, G. &amp; ARGEL, M." box="[699,920,1393,1417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2480" refString="GWYNNE, J. A., RIDGELY, R. S., TUDOR, G. &amp; ARGEL, M. 2010. Aves do Brasil: Pantanal &amp; Cerrado. Wildlife Conservation Society / Editora Horizonte, Sao Paulo, 322 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Gwynne 
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3B82A5E01BA7721A7" box="[798,846,1393,1417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
., 2010
</bibRefCitation>
), there are no documented records for the entire state (Nunes 
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3B9A25EE1BBFC2187" box="[662,709,1425,1449]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
., submitted).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3599AB95F50FFC5BBD75EC9BB952559" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F50FFC3BBD75EC9BAF921DF" blockId="3.[151,1074,1465,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBD75EC9B80A21FF" box="[227,307,1466,1489]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3BBD75EC9B80A21FF" box="[227,307,1466,1489]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Paraná</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
: Scherer-Neto 
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BAE35EC9BB3121FF" box="[471,520,1465,1489]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. (2011) list the species as undocumented in 
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3B8DD5ECABD0B21FF" box="[1001,1074,1465,1489]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">ParanÁ</collectingRegion>
on the basis of its inclusion in an unpublished thesis by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3B9C55EAABA8021DF" author="BORNSCHEIN, M. R." box="[753,953,1497,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2100" refString="BORNSCHEIN, M. R. 2001. Formacoes pioneiras do litoral centro-sul do ParanA: identificacao, quantificacao e caracterizacao ornitofaunistica. Curitiba, Curso de Pos-Graduacao em Engenharia Florestal. Universidade Federal do Parana, Brazil, 194 pp. (Not seen by authors)." type="book" year="2001">Bornschein (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F50FFC4BBD75D71BA602044" blockId="3.[151,1074,1537,1657]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1059,978,1130]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93715205F50FFC3BBD75D71B8BE2237" box="[227,391,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3BBD75D71B8BE2237" box="[227,391,1538,1561]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F50FFC3BAA35D72BB002237" author="ROSARIO, L. A. DO" box="[407,569,1537,1561]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refId="ref2804" refString="ROSARIO, L. A. DO 1996. As aves em Santa Catarina: Distribuicao geogrAfica e meio ambiente. FATMA, Florianopolis, 326 pp." type="book" year="1996">RosÁrio (1996)</bibRefCitation>
maps the species only for coastal northeastern 
<materialsCitation id="3B2BC36F5F50FFC3BBA35D52BAD52277" collectingDate="1979-05-28" location="In" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Santa Catarina">
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3BBA35D52B80A2217" box="[151,307,1569,1593]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
based on a single sight record at “Reserva Florestal Hoffmann, Brusque Municipality” on 
<date id="FFFDEFF25F50FFC3BA685D32B8C82277" box="[348,497,1601,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" value="1979-05-28">
<collectingDate id="EFB9161A5F50FFC3BA685D32B8C82277" box="[348,497,1601,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" value="1979-05-28">28 May 1979</collectingDate>
</date>
. 
<location id="8E9C9FE95F50FFC3B9365D31BB212277" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA78245F50FFC5BBA35877BB952559:8E9C9FE95F50FFC3B9365D31BB212277" box="[514,536,1602,1625]" name="In" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" stateProvince="Santa Catarina">In</location>
fact the only alleged specimen record for
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B2BC36F5F50FFC4B8C25D32B8BC2064" collectingDate="1960-11-18" collectorName="A. Ruschi &amp; Joinville" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="7" location="Joinville" municipality="However" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Santa Catarina">
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F50FFC3B8C25D32B8092257" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Santa Catarina state</collectingRegion>
is MBML-573, supposedly collected by 
<collectorName id="26B6ACE45F50FFC3B8395D12BA462257" box="[781,895,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">A. Ruschi</collectorName>
at 
<collectorName id="26B6ACE45F50FFC3B8995D12BD302257" box="[941,1033,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6">Joinville</collectorName>
on 
<date id="FFFDEFF25F57FFC4BBBC58A1B86C27C4" box="[136,341,978,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" value="1960-11-18">
<collectingDate id="EFB9161A5F57FFC4BBBC58A1B86C27C4" box="[136,341,978,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" value="1960-11-18">18 November 1960</collectingDate>
</date>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B9853485F57FFC4BA5758A0B8FC27C4" box="[355,453,979,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">However</collectingMunicipality>
if the collection data is to be believed the same collector apparently collected several other species of hummingbirds at 
<location id="8E9C9FE95F57FFC4B80C5881BAAD2024" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA78245F50FFC5BBA35877BB952559:8E9C9FE95F57FFC4B80C5881BAAD2024" box="[824,916,1010,1034]" municipality="However" name="Joinville" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" stateProvince="Santa Catarina">Joinville</location>
on the same date, as well as another specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C43B2B15F57FFC4B9265F60BBB02004" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[530,649,1042,1066]" class="Aves" family="Trochilidae" genus="Glaucis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B93715205F57FFC4B9265F60BBB02004" box="[530,649,1042,1066]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">G. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
several thousands of kilometers away at “Usina Rio Branco”
</materialsCitation>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F57FFC4BAA25F41BB1F2064" box="[406,550,1074,1098]" country="Brazil" name="Sergipe" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Sergipe State</collectingRegion>
. Consequently the locality is suspect and the species is not considered documented in the state (Vielliard, 1994).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF3C99BA5F57FFC4B908581FBA1E278E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5822974" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5822974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5822974/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" startId="4.[572,585,876,897]" targetBox="[154,1058,246,855]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F57FFC4B908581FBA1E278E" blockId="4.[388,807,876,928]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">
FIG 3 
<taxonomicName id="4C43B2B15F57FFC4BAB058F9BB1B278E" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[388,546,906,928]" class="Aves" family="Trochilidae" genus="Glaucis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B93715205F57FFC4BAB058F9BB1B278E" box="[388,546,906,928]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Glaucis hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female, MHNG 1723.041.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F57FFC4BBE05F0AB8062255" blockId="4.[136,1059,1144,1659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B93715205F57FFC4BBE05F0AB89A20BE" box="[212,419,1144,1168]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F57FFC4BBE05F0AB89A20BE" box="[212,419,1144,1168]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4BA805F0BBB6C20BE" author="BENCKE, G. A." box="[436,597,1144,1168]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" refId="ref1995" refString="BENCKE, G. A. 2001. Lista de referencia das aves do Rio Grande do Sul. Fundacao Zoobotanica do Rio Grande do Sul, Porto Alegre, 102 pp." type="book" year="2001">Bencke (2001)</bibRefCitation>
cites a Ruschi specimen in the Museu de Biologia Prof. Mello Leitão (MBML 572) supposedly collected on 
<date id="FFFDEFF25F57FFC4B8585FE4BD1B2081" box="[876,1058,1175,1199]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" value="1946-10-31">31 October 1946</date>
at “Fazenda Retiro, Nazareth, Porto Alegre”, but notes several problems with the data. All other specimens of hummingbirds from 
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F57FFC4B9BE5FA7BA5020C2" box="[650,873,1236,1260]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
in the museum collection were collected by Ruschi during his visit to the state in late August and early 
<date id="FFFDEFF25F57FFC4BBBC5E61B80F2104" box="[136,310,1298,1322]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" value="1956-09">September 1956</date>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4BA9A5E61BB7F2104" author="RUSCHI, A." box="[430,582,1298,1322]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 111" refId="ref2832" refString="RUSCHI, A. (1951). Trochilideos do Museu Nacional. Boletim do Museu de Biologia Prof. Mello Leitao, Serie Biologia 10: 1 - 111." type="journal article" year="1951">Ruschi (1951)</bibRefCitation>
claims to “update the distribution of various species of hummingbird not previously recorded in certain Brazilian states”, he omits mention of this species in the southern Brazilian states, including 
<collectingRegion id="498707D05F57FFC4B8655E3CBD252149" box="[849,1052,1359,1383]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
. Later however 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4BA1E5E1DB8FB21A8" author="RUSCHI, A." box="[298,450,1390,1414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref2863" refString="RUSCHI, A. 1965. Os nomes vulgares dos beija-flores do Estado do Rio Grande do Sul (Trochilidae - Aves). Boletim do Museu de Biologia Professor Mello Leitao, Serie Biologia 26: 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1965">Ruschi (1965)</bibRefCitation>
does include the species in the state avifauna along with six other species of hummingbird for which there is apparently no documentation and for which there have been no further records. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4B9475ED8BA2821ED" author="BENCKE, G. A." box="[627,785,1451,1475]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" refId="ref1995" refString="BENCKE, G. A. 2001. Lista de referencia das aves do Rio Grande do Sul. Fundacao Zoobotanica do Rio Grande do Sul, Porto Alegre, 102 pp." type="book" year="2001">Bencke (2001)</bibRefCitation>
hesitantly considered the species a vagrant to the state on the basis of the MBML specimen, but given the uncertainty surrounding the provenance of the specimens and the revelation by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4BBBC5D7BB8082231" author="FONTANA, C. S." box="[136,305,1543,1567]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="161 - 206" refId="ref2417" refString="FONTANA, C. S. 2005. A ornitofauna em Porto Alegre no seculo XX: status de ocorrencia e conservacao. Comunicacoes do Museu de Ciencias e Tecnologia da PUCRS, Serie Zoologia 18: 161 - 206." type="journal article" year="2005">Fontana (2005)</bibRefCitation>
that the locality was untraceable he later discounted it completely (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4BBA55D55B8532210" author="BENCKE, G. A. &amp; DIAS, R. A. &amp; BUGONI, L. &amp; AGNE, C. E. &amp; FONTANA, C. S. &amp; MAURICIO, G. N. &amp; MACHADO, D. B." box="[145,362,1574,1598]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="519 - 556" refId="ref2028" refString="BENCKE, G. A., DIAS, R. A., BUGONI, L., AGNE, C. E., FONTANA, C. S., MAURICIO, G. N., MACHADO, D. B. 2010. Revisao e atualizacao da lista das aves do Rio Grande do Sul, Brasil. Iheringia Serie Zoologia 100: 519 - 556." type="journal article" year="2010">
Bencke 
<emphasis id="B93715205F57FFC4BBDF5D54B81C2210" box="[235,293,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Meyer de Schaunesee (1970, 1982) included the state in the range of the species, but this was rejected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4B9425D37BA3A2272" author="BELTON, W." box="[630,771,1604,1628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="85 - 102" refId="ref1908" refString="BELTON, W. 1978. A list of the birds of Rio Grande do Sul. Iheringia Ser. Zoologia 52: 85 - 102." type="journal article" year="1978">Belton (1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4B8265D37BA7E2272" author="BELTON, W." box="[786,839,1604,1628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" pagination="369 - 636" refId="ref1935" refString="BELTON, W. 1984. Birds of Rio Grande do Sul. Part 1: Rheidae through Furnariidae. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 178: 369 - 636." type="journal article" year="1984">1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2B4C35F57FFC4B8625D37BAB22272" author="BELTON, W." box="[854,907,1604,1628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="7" refId="ref1969" refString="BELTON, W. 1994. Aves do Rio Grande do Sul, distribucao e biologia. Editora Unisinos, Sao Leopoldo, 584 pp." type="book" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
) because of a lack of evidence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCC9325F56FFC5BBD75B90BB952559" blockId="5.[151,1074,227,376]" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">
Though correctly identified, the vagaries of the specimen label regarding both the location and date of collection of the Paraguayan specimen MHNG 1723.041 are cause for similar doubt. Given the distance from, and uncertainty surrounding records in neighbouring states in 
<collectingCountry id="F35489A25F56FFC5BA985A33B8D42576" box="[428,493,320,344]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it would seem preferable to maintain this species as hypothetical in 
<collectingCountry id="F35489A25F56FFC5BA0A5A13B8982556" box="[318,417,352,376]" name="Paraguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
pending further records.
</paragraph>
